<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900719-0059</DOCNO><DOCID>900719-0059.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Graphic Scanning Corp.:   Board Looks for `Alliance'   To Generate New Capital</HL><DATE>07/19/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   GSCC</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   Graphic Scanning Corp. said its directors decided to seekan &quot;alliance&quot; with a &quot;strategic partner or partners&quot; todevelop new businesses and generate new capital.   Based in Englewood, N.J., Graphic Scanning Corp., which isinvolved in paging, cellular telephone and wireless cableoperations, has faltered in previous efforts to improve itsfinancial position. Discussions to sell a controllinginterest in its Digital Mobile Communications Ltd. business,a U.K. telecommunications company, collapsed last year, asdid talks of a possible merger with McCaw CellularCommunications Inc.</LP><TEXT>   The company said its directors had determined thatdeveloping its telecommunications businesses is &quot;beyond thescope&quot; of its current resources. Termination of the DigitalMobile sales discussions &quot;creates immediate capital needs,&quot;the company added.   It said it also is looking at other alternatives to raisecapital, including selling securities or assets or enteringinto other joint ventures.   For the nine months ended March 31, Graphic Scanning had anet loss of $38.5 million, or $1.19 a share, on revenue of$71.1 million.</TEXT></DOC>